    <item>
      <title>About</title>
      <link>/about/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 19 Dec 2024 18:12:03 -0300</pubDate>
      <guid>/about/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;I am junior faculty at the Institute of Physics and Astronomy (IFA) of Universidad de Valparaíso, Chile.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I am interested in developing computational tools for scientific applications, particularly for cosmology and astrophysics. Currently, I contribute to the development of the &lt;a href=&#34;https://hpcsoftware.pages.gitlab.lrz.de/Peano/da/dce/tutorials_exahype2_applications_exagrype.html&#34;&gt;ExaGRyPE&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/crisbh/gramses&#34;&gt;GRAMSES&lt;/a&gt; simulation codes, and apply them to investigate general-relativistic effects. I also lecture and mentor Physics students, specially undergrads majoring in Scientific Computing at IFA-UV.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I was previously a postdoctoral researcher at the Department of Computer Science of the University of Durham, United Kingdom. I did my PhD at the Institute for Computational Cosmology at the University of Durham.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
